        <b>Bengali Food</b>
        <figure>
            <img src="https://www.awesomecuisine.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Bengali-Cuisine.jpg" width="300" height="250">
            <figcaption>Bengali cuisine is renowned for its rich flavors, emphasis on rice and fish, and a wide variety of sweets and savory
            dishes.
            Bengali food originates from the Bengal region, encompassing West Bengal in India and Bangladesh, and is shaped by its
            fertile river deltas, abundant freshwater and seawater fish, and diverse cultural influences including Mughal, Persian,
            and British cuisines.</figcaption>
        </figure>
        
        <b>Gujarati Food</b>
        <figure>
            <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5c6df920d74562c46b234f9e/1587328696559-W520QMT84BQ7F0GIVO91/thaalsite.jpg" width="300" height="250">
            <figcaption>Gujarati cuisine is the cuisine of the Indian state of Gujarat. The typical Gujarati thali consists of rotli, dal or
            curry, rice, and shaak (a dish made up of several different combinations of vegetables and spices, which may be either
            spicy or sweet).</figcaption>
        </figure>

        <b>Mughlai Food</b>
        <figure>
            <img src="https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/msid-82428481,width-748,height-499,resizemode=4,imgsize-1061969/Most-loved-Mughlai-dishes-one-must-try-in-India.jpg"
                width="300" height="250">
            <figcaption>Mughali foods are a testament to the Mughal Empire's culinary legacy, blending Persian elegance with Indian spices. The
            Mughals introduced a variety of dishes that have since become iconic in Indian cuisine.</figcaption>
        </figure>

        <b>Punjabi Food</b>
        <figure>
            <img src="https://www.nehascookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Punjabi-thali-WS.jpg"
                width="350" height="250">
            <figcaption>Punjabi food originates from the Punjab region of South Asia, now divided between India and Pakistan. It is heavily
            influenced by the agrarian lifestyle, with staples including wheat, rice, and dairy products. Punjabi cuisine is famous
            for its use of ghee, butter, cream, and aromatic spices, creating bold, comforting flavors. Traditional cooking often
            involves tandoors (clay ovens), which impart a smoky flavor to breads, meats, and vegetables.</figcaption>
        </figure>

        <b>South Indian Foods</b>
        <figure>
            <img src="https://sukhis.com/app/uploads/2022/04/image3-4.jpg" width="350" height="250">
            <figcaption>South Indian cuisine is a vibrant and diverse culinary tradition that encompasses the food of the five southern states
            of India: Tamil Nadu, Andhra Pradesh, Karnataka, Kerala, and Telangana.Andhra Pradesh cuisine is hotly-spiced and often vegetarian, with seafood prominent along the coast; Kerala too has a
            range of seafood dishes from its coastline. The cuisine of Tamil Nadu is similarly mainly vegetarian, but even
            hotter.In Telangana, Hyderabadi cuisine is somewhat milder but subtle and full of flavour, making use of saffron,
            nuts, and dried fruits as well as warmer spices in dishes for the Nizams.
</figcaption>
        </figure>
